==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trug
<hw>Trug</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Trough</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A trough, or tray.</def>
Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A hod for mortar.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>An old measure of wheat equal to two thirds of a bushel.</def>
<rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A concubine; a harlot.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Taylor (1630).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trugging-house</ent>⟦br⟧
